                        Read this excerpt from the English Bill of Rights, passed by Parliament in 1689.


How does this excerpt try to protect the power of Parliament?


a. It requires approval of the king before Parliament can pass laws.


b. It gives Parliament the power to elect the king.


c.It requires regular meetings of Parliament to change or make laws.

                        

                        
                                                

                        
                        
                            
                                2 months ago
                            

                            

                            

                        

                        

                    

                

                

                
                                            Solution 1

                        
                            
                                
                                
                                    
                                    
                                                                                    
                                            Guest #3607409
                                                                            

                                    

                                    
                                    
                                        2 months ago
                                    

                                    
                                

                                

                                
                                Answer:
C
Explanation:
right on edge


                                

                                
                                                                
                            

                        

                                            Solution 2

                        
                            
                                
                                
                                    
                                    
                                                                                    
                                            Guest #3607410
                                                                            

                                    

                                    
                                    
                                        2 months ago
                                    

                                    
                                

                                

                                
                                It requires regular meetings of Parliament to change or make laws is the excerpt from the English Bill of Rights, passed by Parliament in 1689. Hence, option C is correct.

What is  the English Bill of Rights?

This first Act of the English Parliament has been in the custody of Parliament ever since it was passed. Parliamentary privilege, or the right to free speech, free elections, and regular legislatures were all firmly established by the Bill. To make or alter laws, Parliament must convene frequently.

A constitutional monarchy with legislative limitations on the king or queen's power was formed in England as a result of the English Bill of Rights. Individual rights were protected under this system, and the king was prohibited from ruling without the consent of Parliament.

Thus, option C is correct.
